Description: The identifier property represents any kind of identifier for any kind of Thing
The data when a drug is first approved
A pharmacologic class associated with an approved indication
The specific biochemical interaction through which this drug of supplement produces its pharmacological effect
The generic name of this drug or supplement
Approved patent related to a drug
Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs
The class of drug this belongs to
A route by which this drug may be administered, e.g. 'oral'
A dosage form in which this drug/supplement is available, e.g. 'tablet'
The unit in which the drug is measured
Another drug that is known to interact with this drug
Clinical trial phase of the drug
